240
00:16:25.820 --> 00:16:27.989
[Comandante clears throat]
The pleasure is mine.

241
00:16:28.073 --> 00:16:30.700
Did you have a good trip?

242
00:16:30.784 --> 00:16:32.911
You must be exhausted.

243
00:16:32.994 --> 00:16:35.163
Would you like
some food or water?

244
00:16:35.247 --> 00:16:37.040
Or rest for a while?

245
00:16:37.123 --> 00:16:38.625
I'm fine.

246
00:16:38.708 --> 00:16:40.335
Sit.

247
00:16:47.634 --> 00:16:49.553
You know this is
a mistake. right?

248
00:16:50.178 --> 00:16:51.846
And it will end badly.

249
00:16:53.306 --> 00:16:55.016
[clears throat] The
mistake is theirs.

250
00:16:55.767 --> 00:16:57.519
They thought they
were untouchable.

251
00:16:59.229 --> 00:17:01.231
And if this turns out bad. well.

252
00:17:01.314 --> 00:17:03.108
these are risks we
take during war.

253
00:17:03.191 --> 00:17:05.651
If you really want to
teach a lesson. let her go.

254
00:17:06.319 --> 00:17:08.112
Nobody wants to
return to the past.

255
00:17:09.447 --> 00:17:14.160
Some people do want another
war and we'll give it to them.

256
00:17:14.244 --> 00:17:17.330
If you release her. I'll
write a nice story about you.

257
00:17:17.414 --> 00:17:18.654
[Comandante] I would like that.

258
00:17:18.707 --> 00:17:22.960
But that's a bit too romantic
for things to end up that way.

259
00:17:23.044 --> 00:17:24.379
What are your goals?

260
00:17:25.088 --> 00:17:26.089
Who are you?

261
00:17:27.215 --> 00:17:28.216
I'm just a man.

262
00:17:29.426 --> 00:17:32.053
Trying to create
a new atmosphere.

263
00:17:32.137 --> 00:17:33.597
A new mentality.

264
00:17:34.180 --> 00:17:36.182
And these are my friends.

265
00:17:38.310 --> 00:17:39.352
Talk to her.

266
00:17:40.687 --> 00:17:42.188
Tell me what you think.

267
00:17:43.690 --> 00:17:44.690
Think about what?

268
00:17:45.984 --> 00:17:47.777
Whether or not she is CIA.

269
00:17:48.403 --> 00:17:49.988
You think she will tell me?

270
00:17:50.780 --> 00:17:53.033
Find out. You can do it.

271
00:17:54.034 --> 00:17:55.076
Go ahead.

272
00:17:55.869 --> 00:17:56.870
Okay.

273
00:17:57.621 --> 00:17:59.372
Give me some time
with her. I'll try.

274
00:17:59.915 --> 00:18:01.666
Let's get ready to move.

275
00:18:01.750 --> 00:18:03.043
[guerrilla 3 speaks Spanish]

276
00:18:10.717 --> 00:18:11.718
[speaks Spanish]

277
00:18:23.813 --> 00:18:25.148
[in English] Hello. Amber.

278
00:18:26.524 --> 00:18:30.695
- I'm a journalist. I want to talk to you.
- I... I... I recognize your voice.

279
00:18:31.988 --> 00:18:33.531
- From the radio.
- [Violeta] Yeah.

280
00:18:33.615 --> 00:18:35.367
Your brother is a friend.

281
00:18:36.701 --> 00:18:38.954
And your father-in-law
is my husband's friend.

282
00:18:39.037 --> 00:18:40.080
I wanna help you.

283
00:18:42.457 --> 00:18:43.541
Thank you.

284
00:18:50.465 --> 00:18:52.968
Do you know why you
were taken in this way?

285
00:18:54.636 --> 00:18:56.304
Wrong place. wrong time.

286
00:18:56.972 --> 00:18:59.558
They think I'm CIA.
It's fucking ridiculous.

287
00:19:01.017 --> 00:19:02.310
I know how you feel.

288
00:19:05.021 --> 00:19:06.021
I was kidnapped.

289
00:19:08.608 --> 00:19:12.779
I was in a very small
room during two months.

290
00:19:17.033 --> 00:19:19.035
I hope you don't
go through that.

291
00:19:20.495 --> 00:19:24.541
But if you do. you have
to know you will survive.

292
00:19:27.878 --> 00:19:30.505
They want to know if
you're an American agent.

293
00:19:31.673 --> 00:19:33.425
I don't care if you are or not.

294
00:19:34.634 --> 00:19:39.347
I'm going to talk with the commander
right now and tell him you're innocent.

295
00:19:44.144 --> 00:19:47.105
[whispering] You should stay
with me. It's much safer.

296
00:19:53.862 --> 00:19:59.784
They're all gonna get killed
in this camp. Everyone.

297
00:20:02.454 --> 00:20:04.414
Don't fantasize of a rescue.

298
00:20:05.707 --> 00:20:08.293
They can't find this place
in the middle of the jungle.

299
00:20:08.376 --> 00:20:10.587
You don't know my family.

300
00:20:13.590 --> 00:20:15.800
[Amber] I guarantee you
they tracked you here.

301
00:20:17.969 --> 00:20:19.930
Why do you think my
brother did your show?

302
00:20:22.807 --> 00:20:24.351
You're a bird dog.

303
00:20:26.186 --> 00:20:27.604
You flush out the prey.

304
00:20:28.480 --> 00:20:30.649
[guerrilla 4. in
Spanish] Time's up.

305
00:20:30.732 --> 00:20:31.900
[speaks Spanish]

306
00:20:33.485 --> 00:20:35.565
- [Violeta] Everything will be okay.
- [Amber] Right.

307
00:20:36.905 --> 00:20:38.240
[guerrilla 4 speaks Spanish]

308
00:20:38.740 --> 00:20:39.866
[Prince grunts]

309
00:20:46.957 --> 00:20:48.667
[chattering]

310
00:20:48.750 --> 00:20:50.669
[Bambi. in English] I
have eyes on Violeta.

311
00:20:55.382 --> 00:20:57.551
[Prince] I see at
least 20% of the camp.

312
00:20:59.511 --> 00:21:00.929
Negative on Amber.

313
00:21:03.056 --> 00:21:04.724
[kidnapper 2. in
Spanish] Here she is.

314
00:21:04.808 --> 00:21:05.976
[Comandante] Come here.

315
00:21:07.060 --> 00:21:08.860
- [Comandante] Tell me how it went.
- [sniffs]

316
00:21:10.814 --> 00:21:12.607
I do have something for you.

317
00:21:12.691 --> 00:21:13.733
She's not CIA.

318
00:21:13.817 --> 00:21:16.987
- This is your professional opinion?
- [Violeta] Sí.

319
00:21:17.070 --> 00:21:19.739
After conducting interviews
for 20 years. I can confirm it.

320
00:21:19.823 --> 00:21:21.283
Let her leave with me.

321
00:21:31.376 --> 00:21:33.128
- Graciela.
- [kidnapper 2] Mm-hmm.

322
00:21:33.211 --> 00:21:34.211
Do something for me.

323
00:21:35.547 --> 00:21:37.591
- Take her and tie her up.
- [speaks Spanish]

324
00:21:37.674 --> 00:21:39.068
Then tell everyone
we're moving out.

325
00:21:39.092 --> 00:21:42.012
[both speaking Spanish]

326
00:21:44.306 --> 00:21:45.807
[Graciela] We're moving out.

327
00:21:45.891 --> 00:21:49.519
- [clamoring]
- [Graciela yelling in Spanish]

328
00:21:51.855 --> 00:21:53.857
They're packing up.
getting ready to move.

329
00:21:55.108 --> 00:21:56.109
[Bambi] Colonel?

330
00:21:56.902 --> 00:21:58.737
[soldiers speaking Spanish]

331
00:21:59.404 --> 00:22:00.780
[Pereira speaks Spanish]

332
00:22:01.823 --> 00:22:04.284
We have located the rebel camp.

333
00:22:04.910 --> 00:22:06.596
Where they are holding
the American hostage.

334
00:22:06.620 --> 00:22:08.330
- [clamoring]
- [Graciela speaking Spanish]

335
00:22:08.413 --> 00:22:12.667
[Pereira] Now they have a second
hostage. a journalist. Violeta Matíz.

336
00:22:13.335 --> 00:22:14.770
- [grunts]
- [in English] What's happening?

337
00:22:14.794 --> 00:22:16.213
[Violeta] They believe you.

338
00:22:16.796 --> 00:22:18.236
We are going to
intercept them here.

339
00:22:19.549 --> 00:22:20.749
We are going to surround them.

340
00:22:21.509 --> 00:22:23.261
We are going to
make them desperate.

341
00:22:24.095 --> 00:22:26.932
- [guerrillas speaking Spanish]
- [Amber groaning]

342
00:22:30.894 --> 00:22:34.189
[Pereira] Force them to
negotiate. to make mistakes.

343
00:22:35.106 --> 00:22:37.025
There are a lot of
eyes watching us.

344
00:22:39.694 --> 00:22:40.694
Get ready.

345
00:22:42.447 --> 00:22:43.615
Any questions?

346
00:22:43.698 --> 00:22:45.659
[soldiers speaking Spanish]

347
00:22:46.451 --> 00:22:47.452
That's the way I like it.

348
00:22:48.370 --> 00:22:49.454
Commandos. move out!

349
00:22:50.580 --> 00:22:51.831
[soldiers speaking Spanish]

350
00:23:11.017 --> 00:23:13.687
[radio chatter]

351
00:23:32.205 --> 00:23:34.249
[soldier 2] They're
headed to the river.

352
00:23:36.167 --> 00:23:38.879
[Pereira] Do not engage.
We're 10 minutes out.

353
00:24:40.774 --> 00:24:42.567
[speaks Spanish]

354
00:24:43.360 --> 00:24:44.903
[guerrillas speaking Spanish]

355
00:24:50.242 --> 00:24:53.161
[all shouting]

356
00:24:58.041 --> 00:24:59.834
[radio chatter in Spanish]

357
00:25:04.381 --> 00:25:06.758
[helicopter whirring]

358
00:25:08.969 --> 00:25:10.804
[radio chatter continues]

359
00:25:30.699 --> 00:25:32.117
[guerrilla 5 speaks Spanish]

360
00:25:39.874 --> 00:25:40.874
[all shouting]

361
00:26:58.954 --> 00:27:02.249
[Pereira] This is Colonel Pereira
of the Colombian National Army.

362
00:27:03.083 --> 00:27:05.710
You are completely surrounded.

363
00:27:05.794 --> 00:27:08.213
This is now my battleground.

364
00:27:09.005 --> 00:27:11.591
I decide what happens to you.

365
00:27:12.884 --> 00:27:16.638
No one will leave here alive with
Amber Chesborough or Violeta Matíz.

366
00:27:19.933 --> 00:27:22.143
You will all die
here one by one.

367
00:27:22.227 --> 00:27:24.563
Unless you release the hostages.

368
00:27:24.646 --> 00:27:26.147
[speaks Spanish]

369
00:27:26.231 --> 00:27:27.524
[Pereira] I have plenty of time.

370
00:27:27.607 --> 00:27:28.900
[speaks Spanish]

371
00:27:30.777 --> 00:27:31.778
[Pereira] You decide.

372
00:27:34.573 --> 00:27:36.741
[helicopter whirring]

373
00:27:46.042 --> 00:27:49.754
[Comandante speaking Spanish]

374
00:27:50.797 --> 00:27:52.007
I have the Comandante.

375
00:27:55.385 --> 00:27:56.386
Fire.

376
00:27:56.469 --> 00:27:59.347
- [speaks Spanish]
- [gunshot]

377
00:28:02.475 --> 00:28:04.352
We just killed your Comandante.

378
00:28:04.436 --> 00:28:05.896
It was easy.

379
00:28:10.859 --> 00:28:12.736
[Pereira] I can stay
here indefinitely.

380
00:28:14.738 --> 00:28:16.031
For hours…

381
00:28:17.699 --> 00:28:18.700
for weeks.

382
00:28:21.202 --> 00:28:22.454
You decide.

383
00:28:24.956 --> 00:28:26.833
[Pereira speaking Spanish]

384
00:28:28.752 --> 00:28:31.338
[continues speaking Spanish]

385
00:28:54.527 --> 00:28:55.654
[pants]

386
00:28:55.737 --> 00:28:57.197
Make the fucking call.

387
00:29:08.833 --> 00:29:10.835
- [upbeat music playing]
- [cell phone chimes]

388
00:29:31.898 --> 00:29:34.401
[people screaming. clamoring]

389
00:29:34.985 --> 00:29:37.654
[technician] They just
blew up a café in Bogotá.

390
00:29:50.208 --> 00:29:51.126
[phone beeps]

391
00:29:51.209 --> 00:29:53.670
This is Foster. Connect
me to the SecDef. please.

392
00:29:56.172 --> 00:29:58.133
Sir. we have a credible threat.

393
00:29:58.216 --> 00:30:00.278
They're claiming to have more
bombs throughout the city.

394
00:30:00.302 --> 00:30:02.679
[speaking Spanish]

395
00:30:12.439 --> 00:30:14.119
[Pereira] General. we
have them surrounded!

396
00:30:14.190 --> 00:30:15.775
I can capture them all!

397
00:30:15.859 --> 00:30:20.030
[Bolero] It doesn't matter. They
threatened to bomb more civilians.

398
00:30:20.113 --> 00:30:22.866
This comes from the top. From
the White House and the CIA.

399
00:30:22.949 --> 00:30:24.034
Do you understand?

400
00:30:24.117 --> 00:30:26.036
They don't want more
civilian casualties.

401
00:30:26.828 --> 00:30:27.829
[device beeps]

402
00:30:32.500 --> 00:30:34.211
[Pereira] Attention. everyone.

403
00:30:34.294 --> 00:30:36.254
Abort. abort. abort.

404
00:30:37.172 --> 00:30:38.506
Retreat.

405
00:30:38.590 --> 00:30:40.050
We're headed back to base.

406
00:30:44.429 --> 00:30:46.429
- [sighs]
- [in English] There's nothing we can do.

407
00:31:07.202 --> 00:31:09.829
[Spanish music playing]

408
00:31:42.862 --> 00:31:46.575
[guerrillas cheering. laughing]

409
00:31:51.288 --> 00:31:53.408
- [cheering. chanting]
- [guerrilla 5 yells] Fuck you!

410
00:31:53.832 --> 00:31:56.126
- [laughing. cheering]
- Yes! Fuck you!

411
00:32:03.049 --> 00:32:04.426
[guerrilla 6] Fuck you!

412
00:32:04.509 --> 00:32:09.264
[guerrillas chanting] Fuck you! Fuck
you! Fuck you! Fuck you! Fuck you!

413
00:32:09.347 --> 00:32:10.974
[chanting continues]

414
00:32:17.230 --> 00:32:18.815
- [chuckles]
- I love you.

415
00:32:24.321 --> 00:32:25.530
[sighs]

416
00:33:28.677 --> 00:33:31.096
[breathing heavily]

417
00:33:31.179 --> 00:33:33.598
[speaks Spanish]

418
00:33:33.682 --> 00:33:35.267
Trust me. Colonel.

419
00:33:35.350 --> 00:33:36.851
I know. Politics.

420
00:33:36.935 --> 00:33:40.188
But we are under a lot
of pressure to withdraw.

421
00:33:41.523 --> 00:33:42.732
It's a sad day.

422
00:33:42.816 --> 00:33:44.526
General. the day isn't over.

423
00:33:45.360 --> 00:33:47.821
It will take them 9 hours
to get to the border.

424
00:33:47.904 --> 00:33:51.575
Sir. if you can give me a bird.
we can take one more shot at this.

425
00:33:51.658 --> 00:33:54.327
The media has us
in a bad position.

426
00:33:55.787 --> 00:33:57.122
It's our country. sir.

427
00:33:57.205 --> 00:33:58.206
[Bolero] You're right.

428
00:33:58.915 --> 00:34:00.125
It's our country.

429
00:34:01.126 --> 00:34:02.961
I say this unofficially.

430
00:34:03.545 --> 00:34:07.007
Take volunteers and do
what you think is right.

431
00:34:08.967 --> 00:34:10.594
[in English] Commandos…

432
00:34:12.846 --> 00:34:14.681
[in Spanish] I need
nine volunteers.

433
00:34:14.764 --> 00:34:17.142
[soldiers speaking Spanish]

434
00:34:27.318 --> 00:34:28.528
[Pereira] Caballeros.

435
00:34:28.612 --> 00:34:32.324
[in English] We aren't done.
Load up. We leave at dawn.

436
00:34:36.912 --> 00:34:38.954
[vehicle approaching]

437
00:35:08.526 --> 00:35:10.070
[guerrillas shouting in Spanish]

438
00:35:22.040 --> 00:35:23.208
[shouting in Spanish]

439
00:36:01.204 --> 00:36:02.682
[pilot. in English]
Signal intelligence say

440
00:36:02.706 --> 00:36:05.208
they are in trucks on
a slow jungle road.

441
00:36:05.292 --> 00:36:07.311
[Pereira. in Spanish] We can
cut across the jungle by air

442
00:36:07.335 --> 00:36:08.795
and beat them to the border.

443
00:36:10.046 --> 00:36:12.173
This spot here is
the perfect ambush.

444
00:36:13.133 --> 00:36:14.259
Three guys on the ridge.

445
00:36:14.342 --> 00:36:15.594
The rest with me.

446
00:36:15.677 --> 00:36:17.012
We'll attack from the ground.

447
00:36:57.761 --> 00:37:00.222
[Pereira] IED armed and ready.

448
00:37:00.305 --> 00:37:01.306
[Bambi] Check.

449
00:37:40.929 --> 00:37:45.725
All stations. all stations. I
will initiate on the lead vehicle.

450
00:37:52.148 --> 00:37:55.652
[breathing heavily]

451
00:38:10.125 --> 00:38:12.002
- [gunfire]
- [glass shatters]

452
00:38:18.008 --> 00:38:19.593
[tires screeching]

453
00:38:24.973 --> 00:38:26.850
[breathes shakily]

454
00:38:27.976 --> 00:38:28.977
[exhales sharply]

455
00:38:37.027 --> 00:38:38.445
[Prince] Bambi. what do you got?

456
00:38:38.528 --> 00:38:41.823
[breathing heavily]

457
00:38:50.165 --> 00:38:51.416
[gunshot]

458
00:38:52.667 --> 00:38:55.086
[whimpering]

459
00:38:59.049 --> 00:39:01.301
[breathes heavily] Not
a lot of targets here.

460
00:39:01.384 --> 00:39:02.219
Roger.

461
00:39:02.302 --> 00:39:04.137
[engine revs]

462
00:39:05.305 --> 00:39:06.598
[gunshot]

463
00:39:21.154 --> 00:39:22.405
[gunfire]

464
00:39:25.325 --> 00:39:27.619
[gunfire continues]

465
00:39:33.875 --> 00:39:35.252
[gasps]

466
00:39:38.547 --> 00:39:39.547
[grunts]

467
00:39:42.801 --> 00:39:44.553
[breathing heavily]

468
00:39:45.720 --> 00:39:46.846
[gunshot]

469
00:39:58.066 --> 00:39:59.818
[breathing heavily]

470
00:40:23.008 --> 00:40:24.593
[breathing heavily]

471
00:40:26.720 --> 00:40:29.389
[whispering in Spanish]

472
00:40:39.816 --> 00:40:40.942
What are you seeing?

473
00:40:42.777 --> 00:40:44.377
[breathes heavily]
Bambi. I got nothing.

474
00:40:55.957 --> 00:40:58.209
Fuck. [breathes heavily]

475
00:40:59.794 --> 00:41:01.463
[Prince] They're covered.

476
00:41:03.673 --> 00:41:05.675
[breathes shakily]
All stations hold.

477
00:41:14.935 --> 00:41:16.686
I've got more vehicles inbound.

478
00:41:19.189 --> 00:41:21.650
[breathes heavily] Prince.
you've gotta fucking go.

479
00:41:21.733 --> 00:41:23.360
I can't see Amber.

480
00:41:24.819 --> 00:41:25.987
Thirty seconds out.

481
00:41:27.614 --> 00:41:30.283
Go! Fucking do something!

482
00:41:32.452 --> 00:41:35.830
- Prince. go now!
- [breathes heavily]

483
00:41:35.914 --> 00:41:37.958
- [gunshot]
- [guerilla grunts. yelps]

484
00:41:39.376 --> 00:41:41.461
- [gunshots]
- [grunts]

485
00:41:41.545 --> 00:41:43.296
[guerrilla 2 speaks Spanish]

486
00:41:45.549 --> 00:41:48.301
Prince. go. fucking go! Now!

487
00:41:49.094 --> 00:41:52.722
- [grunting. groaning]
- Colonel. I got Violeta! I got Violeta!

488
00:41:55.433 --> 00:41:57.727
[Violeta crying. groaning]

489
00:41:59.521 --> 00:42:00.814
[guerrillas clamoring]

490
00:42:03.608 --> 00:42:05.443
[breathing heavily]

491
00:42:06.861 --> 00:42:07.946
I'm moving down.

492
00:42:08.822 --> 00:42:10.902
- Hold those trucks and cover me!
- [soldier 2] Yeah!

493
00:42:10.949 --> 00:42:12.534
[panting]

494
00:42:28.967 --> 00:42:31.261
[panting. grunting]

495
00:42:40.395 --> 00:42:42.939
[breathing heavily]

496
00:43:09.925 --> 00:43:11.593
I got Amber!

497
00:43:11.676 --> 00:43:13.220
[pants]

498
00:43:23.939 --> 00:43:26.316
- [gunshots]
- [Prince yelps. grunts]

499
00:43:30.070 --> 00:43:31.571
